---
// /sdk/cesium-ion/quickstart — Quickstart for @splatforge/cesium-ion.
//
// Companion to /sdk. Cesium ion tile fetcher that streams
// SplatForge-optimized tile sets into a CesiumJS or ion viewer
// alongside terrain and 3D-tiles imagery.
import Base from "../../../layouts/Base.astro";

const title = "Cesium ion plugin — SplatForge SDK quickstart";
const description =
  "Quickstart for @splatforge/cesium-ion. Stream SplatForge-optimized splat tile sets into a CesiumJS viewer next to your existing terrain and 3D-tiles imagery.";
---

<Base title={title} description={description}>
  <nav class="nav" aria-label="Primary">
    <a href="/" class="nav-brand">
      <span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      splatforge
    </a>
    <div class="nav-links">
      <a href="/">Home</a>
      <a href="/bench">SplatBench</a>
      <a href="/pricing">Pricing</a>
      <a href="/sdk" aria-current="page">SDK</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/montabano1/SplatForge" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">GitHub ↗</a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <div class="breadcrumb">
    <a href="/sdk">← SDK overview</a>
  </div>

  <header class="hero hero-sdk">
    <h1>Cesium ion quickstart</h1>
    <p>
      <code>@splatforge/cesium-ion</code> is a tile fetcher that streams
      SplatForge-optimized splat tile sets into a
      <strong>CesiumJS</strong> viewer alongside terrain, 3D-tiles
      imagery, and your other ion assets. Same tiling pyramid Cesium
      already speaks (3D-tiles 1.1, implicit tiling) — the splat
      payload travels inside the <code>.glb</code> tile content.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="quickstart">
    <h2>1. Install</h2>
    <pre><code>npm install cesium @splatforge/cesium-ion</code></pre>

    <h2>2. Register the splat tile content handler</h2>
    <pre><code set:html={`import * as Cesium from "cesium";
import { registerSplatForgeTileHandler } from "@splatforge/cesium-ion";

// Call once during app init, BEFORE creating the viewer.
registerSplatForgeTileHandler(Cesium);`} /></pre>

    <h2>3. Add a SplatForge tile set to the viewer</h2>
    <pre><code set:html={`const viewer = new Cesium.Viewer("cesiumContainer", {
  terrainProvider: await Cesium.createWorldTerrainAsync(),
});

const splatTiles = await Cesium.Cesium3DTileset.fromUrl(
  "https://your-cdn.example.com/splat-tilesets/bonsai/tileset.json",
);
viewer.scene.primitives.add(splatTiles);
await viewer.zoomTo(splatTiles);`} /></pre>

    <p>
      The tile set is plain 3D-tiles 1.1 — host it on S3, R2,
      Cesium ion, or any CDN. The handler recognizes SplatForge tile
      content by its extension marker and routes those tiles through
      the splat renderer; standard mesh tiles in the same set keep
      using Cesium's stock renderer.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Issue a license key (above 10k MAU)</h2>
    <p>
      Below 10k MAU per app per month the plugin runs without a key.
      Above the free tier, issue an HMAC-SHA256 JWT bound to your
      <code>Origin</code> domain:
    </p>
    <pre><code set:html={`curl -X POST https://splatforge.dev/api/v1/sdk/license \\
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $SPLATFORGE_API_KEY" \\
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \\
  -d '{"origin": "https://your-app.example.com"}'`} /></pre>
    <p>
      Pass it when registering the tile handler:
    </p>
    <pre><code set:html={`registerSplatForgeTileHandler(Cesium, {
  licenseKey: import.meta.env.PUBLIC_SPLATFORGE_LICENSE,
});`} /></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="next-steps">
    <h2>Next</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/sdk">SDK overview &amp; pricing</a></li>
      <li><a href="/vs-cesium-ion">SplatForge vs Cesium ion (comparison)</a></li>
      <li><a href="/pricing">Hosted optimize API pricing</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/montabano1/SplatForge" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Source on GitHub ↗</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .breadcrumb {
    max-width: 64rem;
    margin: 1.5rem auto 0;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }
  .breadcrumb a { color: inherit; opacity: 0.7; }
  .quickstart, .next-steps {
    max-width: 64rem;
    margin: 2rem auto;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .quickstart h2, .next-steps h2 { margin-top: 2rem; }
  .quickstart pre {
    overflow-x: auto;
    padding: 1rem;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
  }
  .next-steps ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
  .next-steps li { margin: 0.5rem 0; }
</style>
